ce:section.ce:para:
We have obtained the calculation method of imprinting factor and selectivity coefficient through Refs. [77,78]. The imprinting factor should be determined from the ratio of slopes of calibration plots for MIP sensor (0.354 μA/ ng·mL−1) (Table 2
                        ) and NIP sensor (0.021 μA/ ng·mL−1) (Table 2). The imprinting factor was 16.9. Moreover, the selectivity coefficient to each interfering compound could be determined as the ratio of the slope of the calibration plot for IgG and a given compound including HSA, BSA and Lyz (Fig. 10
                        , Table 2). And the calculated selectivity coefficient of HSA, BSA and Lyz were 7.4, 8.4 and 9.3 respectively. Advantageously, the sensor did not respond to HSA, BSA and Lyz. Consequently, the as-prepared IgG biosensor in this study exhibited favorable selectivity for the target IgG. Such an experimental result showed that the biosensor might be used in accurately measuring IgG concentration within practical specimens.
